HEADWORD: Ambitus
<hw>Am"bi*tus</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧m"b⟦icr⟧*t⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. See <er>Ambit</er>, <er>Ambition</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The exterior edge or border of a thing, as the border of a leaf, or
the outline of a bivalve shell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A canvassing for
votes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ambivalency</ent>⟦br⟧
